canonical:
  title: 賀李通憲齊賢學士宴
  author: 尹奕
  language: lzh
  text: 高門盛事復何言靑鬢提衡且莫論一宴共歡三座主四觴齊壽兩家尊讓前讓後蟬冠擁迎北迎南鳳盖飜賓從林林無可選盡敎桃李閒蘭蓀
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀李通憲齊賢學士宴
  author: 尹奕
  language: lzh
  text: 高門盛事復何言。靑鬢提衡且莫論。一宴共歡三座主。四觴齊壽兩家尊。讓前讓後蟬冠擁。迎北迎南鳳盖飜。賓從林林無可選。盡敎桃李閒蘭蓀。
korean:
  title: 통헌 이제현의 학사연을 하례하며
  author: 윤혁
  language: kor
  text: |-
    높은 문의 성사를 다시 말해 무엇하리
    젊어서 문형된 것 그뿐 아닐세
    한 잔치에 세 좌주(과거에 합격시켜준 시관(試官))가 함께 기뻐하고
    네 술잔으로 두 댁 어른께 헌수하네
    앞에 뒤에 자리를 사양, 선관들이 옹위하고
    북으로 남으로 맞아들이는 봉의 일산들이 펄럭이네
    자리에 찬 인재들 모두 아름다우니
    복숭아ㆍ오얏 사이에 난초ㆍ혜초가 섞였네
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0180_010_0150&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001] 복숭아ㆍ오얏 …… 섞였네 : '
    value: 당나라 적인걸(狄仁傑)이 인물을 뽑아 벼슬에 오른 이가 많으니 사람들이 말하기를, “천하의 도리(桃李)가 모두 공(公)의 문중에 있다.” 하였고, 난초는 집안의 자제(子弟)를 말한 것이다. 진(晉)나라 사현(謝玄)이 그의 숙부 사안(謝安)에게 말하기를, “부형이 아름다운 자제를 원하는 것을 비유하면 지란(芝蘭)과 옥수(玉樹)가 내 뜰안에 나기를 바라는 것과 같습니다.” 하였다.
english:
  title: In Celebration of Minister Lee Je-hyeon's Scholars' Banquet
  author: Yun Hyeok
  language: eng
  text: |-
    What more need be said of such splendor in a noble house?
    The young man's literary brilliance is not merely this.
    At one feast, three examiners rejoice together,
    And four cups are raised in honor to both families' elders.
    Bowing before and after, the officials cluster in deference,
    While from north and south the phoenix canopies flutter in welcome.
    The hall overflows with talents beyond all choosing—
    Peach and plum trees now intermingle with orchid and fragrant grasses.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The peach and plum trees symbolize the many successful candidates promoted through the examiner's discernment, alluding to the Tang official Di Renjie, of whom it was said 'all the peaches and plums of the realm belong to his household.' The orchid and fragrant grasses represent the noble descendants of the family itself, referencing Xie Xuan's words to his uncle Xie An about desiring virtuous relatives as one desires aromatic plants in one's garden.
  - key: ''
    value: The three examiners (座主) likely refers to the multiple examination officials or mentors who had advanced Lee Je-hyeon's career; the two families' elders refer to both sides of the examined official's family connections.
